fields.name: Leflaive Puligny Montrachet 1er Cru Clavoillon
fields.description: The vision of Anne-Claude Leflaive in the 1990s took this Puligny Montrachet Domaine to the heights of white wine production, not only in Burgundy but in the rest of the world. Today, her nephew Brice de La Morandière - who has had a successful career running multinational companies - continues her philosophy of organic, biodynamic viticulture, bringing Chardonnay grapes to their best possible expression in Grand Cru and Premier Cru climates, where the terroir has been restored to health by natural practices.

fields.name: Château Haut Brion 2006
fields.description: 2006 saw a powerful Haut-Brion of the highest quality released. This vintage, Merlot took precedence over Cabernet in the blend, producing a deep, succulent red Bordeaux for drinking over the next 20 years plus.

fields.name: Louis Jadot Clos Vougeot Grand Cru 2013
fields.description: From the callars of leading French wine producer Louis Jadot, this Clos Vougeot Grand Cru 2013 is a superb Red Burgundy which can be enjoyed now, or cellared for another decade. Fragrant dark fruit nose of ripe berries, on the palate silky texture with great depth and complexity.

fields.name: Château Mouton Rothschild 1996
fields.description: From a great vintage now drinking at its peak, the 1996 Bordeaux 1st Growth Pauillac Mouton Rothschild has mellowed over time, showing a complex array of blackcurrant, cedar and spice notes soaring from the glass and broad yet resolved tannins that make this great wine a pleasure to drink.
